== Overview ==
NeoLight turns your mobile device into a flashlight.

It flips the brightness up to full and displays a fullscreen bright white rectangle. 

It's written in Python / [http://trac.enlightenment.org/e/wiki/Elementary Elementary].

The Project is hosted on [http://code.google.com/p/neolight/ Google code].

== Features ==
* Bright white or colored (red/green/blue/custom) screen
* Brightness dimmer
* Strobe light modes (with adjustable speed)
* Just tap the top left corner of screen to dim brightness to minimum, and the top right corner to flip the brightness up to the level defined in settings.

== Download and installation ==
You can install NeoLight directly from Web with opkg. All packages are available [http://code.google.com/p/neolight/downloads/list here].
For example:
<pre>
opkg install http://neolight.googlecode.com/files/neolight_1.3.2-r0_all.ipk
</pre>

